WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.430
<b>Cape Promise</b>

21
00:02:06.860 --> 00:02:08.320
It's a flower!

22
00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:08.320
A flower?

23
00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.280
Oh, never mind. It's a person.

24
00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:16.570
What is he?

25
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:20.120
That old guy killed an imperial
squid in one fell swoop...

26
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:21.870
Was he just fishing...

27
00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:24.960
or was he trying to save us...?

28
00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:54.700
Say something already, jerk!

29
00:02:57.660 --> 00:03:00.200
I-If you wanna fight,
we'll fight, you bastard!

30
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:01.910
We've got cannons!

31
00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:05.290
You'd better stop what you're
doing before someone dies.

32
00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:09.920
Oh, yeah?

33
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:11.170
And just who's gonna die?

34
00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:12.380
Me.

35
00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:13.630
You?!

36
00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:14.420
You damn...

37
00:03:14.420 --> 00:03:15.470
Hey, calm down.

38
00:03:15.470 --> 00:03:17.890
That bastard's mocking us...

39
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:21.180
Hey, gramps!

40
00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:24.230
How about you tell us
who you are and where we are.

41
00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:26.480
If you're going to ask a question,

42
00:03:27.150 --> 00:03:31.320
don't you think it's polite
to introduce yourself first?

43
00:03:31.320 --> 00:03:34.610
Huh? Oh, yeah, good point.

44
00:03:34.610 --> 00:03:35.780
Sorry about that.

45
00:03:35.780 --> 00:03:38.490
– My name is Crocus.
– I'm Roro... noa...

46
00:03:38.490 --> 00:03:41.700
I'm the lighthouse keeper
of the Twin Capes.

47
00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:43.540
I'm seventy-one and a Gemini.

48
00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:46.210
My blood type is AB.

49
00:03:43.910 --> 00:03:46.210
Let me cut him down!

50
00:03:44.750 --> 00:03:46.210
Hey, calm down.

51
00:03:46.210 --> 00:03:48.370
You want to know where we are?

52
00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:56.470
How dare you barge into my private
resort and run your mouth at me?

53
00:03:57.260 --> 00:04:00.800
Where do you think
we are? A rat's belly?

54
00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:03.640
S-So we were eaten
by the whale after all...

55
00:04:04.350 --> 00:04:07.020
But is this really the inside
of a whale's stomach?

56
00:04:07.020 --> 00:04:09.940
Wait! What's gonna happen to us?!

57
00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:12.820
I don't wanna be digested!

58
00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:14.730
The exit is over there.

59
00:04:14.730 --> 00:04:16.240
– We can get out?!
– We can get out?!

60
00:04:17.110 --> 00:04:20.660
Hold on a sec! Why is there
an exit in a whale's stomach?!

61
00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:22.950
And why is the door in the sky?!

62
00:04:22.950 --> 00:04:25.660
Wait... Look at it carefully...

63
00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:29.920
This sky... Those seagulls...

64
00:04:30.580 --> 00:04:31.830
They're all painted!

65
00:04:31.830 --> 00:04:34.210
It's all a painting inside
the whale's stomach!

66
00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:35.420
Huh?!

67
00:04:35.420 --> 00:04:37.050
Call it a doctor's whimsy.

68
00:04:37.050 --> 00:04:39.430
What the hell are you
doing in here, you bastard?!

69
00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:41.140
That's enough. Just ignore him.

70
00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:42.220
Agreed.

71
00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:44.760
Nami! We found the exit,
so let's just get out of here.

72
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:46.180
Yeah.

73
00:04:50.810 --> 00:04:52.270
What's going on?!

74
00:04:53.650 --> 00:04:54.980
It's started again...

75
00:04:56.110 --> 00:04:56.980
Look at that!

76
00:04:57.780 --> 00:04:59.110
That's not an island!

77
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:01.410
It's a ship! One that's made of iron!

78
00:05:01.410 --> 00:05:04.910
Oh, of course! It's because
this sea is gastric acid!

79
00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:08.580
Then our wooden ship's gonna
dissolve if we stay here too long.

80
00:05:08.580 --> 00:05:10.790
Hey! What's started?!

81
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:12.790
Tell us!

82
00:05:13.460 --> 00:05:14.960
It's this whale...

83
00:05:16.460 --> 00:05:20.930
Laboon has started ramming
his head into the Red Line.

84
00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:31.270
– What?!
– What?!

85
00:05:31.270 --> 00:05:35.270
Come to think of it, the whale
had terrible scars on his forehead.

86
00:05:35.270 --> 00:05:37.400
And the way he howled at the sky...

87
00:05:37.400 --> 00:05:38.990
So what?

88
00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:41.450
He's suffering!

89
00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:51.870
Oh, so that's what
the geezer's doing here!

90
00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:52.790
Most likely.

91
00:05:52.790 --> 00:05:55.840
He's probably trying to kill
the whale from the inside!

92
00:05:55.840 --> 00:05:56.670
Now...

93
00:05:56.670 --> 00:05:58.920
What a vicious way to kill it!

94
00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:01.300
Alright, mystery solved.
Now let's go, quick.

95
00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:03.130
We'll be digested if we stay too long.

96
00:06:04.300 --> 00:06:07.140
We have nothing to say
about his whale hunting,

97
00:06:07.140 --> 00:06:09.350
nor do we have any reason
to save the whale.

98
00:06:09.350 --> 00:06:10.640
Let's get out of here.

99
00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:28.280
Dammit! With the waves
surging like this,

100
00:06:28.280 --> 00:06:30.410
I don't know if we can
even reach the doors!

101
00:06:30.410 --> 00:06:32.710
We're gonna have
to paddle! Grab the oars!

102
00:06:32.710 --> 00:06:35.670
Let's speed it up!
I'm worried about Luffy.

103
00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:37.040
He's outside!

104
00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:39.000
I saw him fly out of the mouth!

105
00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:43.760
The old man dove in!

106
00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:44.550
Huh?

107
00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:47.550
What's he doing?
He's gonna be dissolved.

108
00:06:57.940 --> 00:07:00.320
What?! What's going on?!
Huh? Why?!

109
00:07:00.320 --> 00:07:01.570
Dizzy... Dizzy...

110
00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:03.950
I'm getting dizzy!

111
00:07:11.950 --> 00:07:13.200
What now?

112
00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:16.000
Is this the sea? A river? A canal?

113
00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:29.930
Okay. We've infiltrated
this far successfully.

114
00:07:29.970 --> 00:07:32.390
<b>Miss Wednesday
Mysterious Woman</b>

115
00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:32.390
Listen, Miss Wednesday.

116
00:07:32.390 --> 00:07:34.640
The stomach is right
behind these doors,

117
00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:37.270
and that geezer is
most likely there too.

118
00:07:37.270 --> 00:07:39.900
We must eliminate him.

119
00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:42.780
<b>Mr. 9
Mysterious Man</b>

120
00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:42.780
Our goal is the whale.

121
00:07:43.150 --> 00:07:44.780
That's right, Mr. 9.

122
00:07:44.780 --> 00:07:49.240
This whale will be precious,
sweet honey to our town.

123
00:07:51.990 --> 00:07:54.080
Hey! The geezer came back up!

124
00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:55.080
Forget about him.

125
00:07:55.080 --> 00:07:58.580
More importantly, how are
we gonna open those doors?

126
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:01.590
Okay, Miss Wednesday,

127
00:08:01.590 --> 00:08:04.090
we'll open them on
"Three, two, one, baby!"

128
00:08:04.090 --> 00:08:05.210
Be on your guard.

129
00:08:05.210 --> 00:08:08.180
Roger, Mr. 9.
I'm ready when you are.

130
00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:15.850
I can't stop!

131
00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:13.470
What is this voice, Mr. 9?

132
00:08:13.470 --> 00:08:15.850
I don't know, Miss Wednesday.

133
00:08:26.070 --> 00:08:27.190
Not them again...!

134
00:08:29.740 --> 00:08:31.530
This is bad, Miss Wednesday!

135
00:08:31.530 --> 00:08:34.080
There's a sea of gastric acid below us!

136
00:08:35.660 --> 00:08:36.500
Luffy?

137
00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:39.080
Hey! So everyone's okay?

138
00:08:40.120 --> 00:08:42.500
Anyway... help me!

139
00:08:47.050 --> 00:08:50.760
Two more weirdos
came down with Luffy...

140
00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.930
Hey! That old man disappeared!

141
00:08:52.930 --> 00:08:55.970
Forget him. We gotta save Luffy!

142
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:12.700
Stop it, Laboon.

143
00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:16.290
Don't hurt yourself any more.

144
00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:18.750
There isn't much sedative left...

145
00:09:18.750 --> 00:09:21.210
I'll have to make some more.

146
00:09:23.710 --> 00:09:27.300
That wall divides the world's oceans.

147
00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:32.300
It won't break, even if you hit it
until you die, Laboon.

148
00:09:37.220 --> 00:09:38.600
It's calmed down!

149
00:09:38.600 --> 00:09:40.350
The whale is quiet now.

150
00:09:40.350 --> 00:09:42.230
Seems like it.

151
00:09:42.730 --> 00:09:43.850
Now...

152
00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:48.320
We ended up saving you guys
too, but who are you?

153
00:09:49.150 --> 00:09:52.110
Mr. 9, these people are pirates.

154
00:09:52.110 --> 00:09:54.280
I-I know, Miss Wednesday.

155
00:09:54.990 --> 00:09:59.790
B-But if we explain it to them,
they should understand... perhaps...

156
00:09:59.790 --> 00:10:02.250
You thugs are still at it?

157
00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:05.170
How many times do
I need to tell you?!

158
00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:10.340
You'll never lay a finger on
Laboon as long as I live!

159
00:10:12.930 --> 00:10:14.140
He's back.

160
00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:15.800
Who's that old guy?

161
00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:20.680
No matter what you say,
we can't just leave.

162
00:10:20.680 --> 00:10:23.390
Our mission is to
take down this whale.

163
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:26.270
You won't interfere with
our whale hunting this time!

164
00:10:26.270 --> 00:10:29.320
We'll blast a hole in his stomach!

165
00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:31.070
Let's go, baby!

166
00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:31.070
Roger!

167
00:10:36.780 --> 00:10:38.910
Those bastards!

168
00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:45.420
The old guy jumped
right into the shots!

169
00:10:45.420 --> 00:10:47.920
Was he... protecting the whale?!

170
00:10:51.340 --> 00:10:52.880
Stop this futile resistance!

171
00:10:52.880 --> 00:10:55.050
Protect this whale all you want!

172
00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:58.800
But this whale will become
food for our town!

173
00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:06.190
What's going on?

174
00:11:14.150 --> 00:11:15.650
They just...

175
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:16.910
had it coming.

176
00:11:21.830 --> 00:11:25.580
I thank you for saving me... but why?

177
00:11:25.580 --> 00:11:27.170
I wasn't trying to save you.

178
00:11:27.170 --> 00:11:29.460
I just didn't like them.

179
00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:33.420
Hey, Luffy! What're you doing?
So, who are these guys?

180
00:11:33.420 --> 00:11:36.340
And what are you doing
inside this whale?

181
00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:36.340
Stop it!

182
00:11:36.340 --> 00:11:39.760
Hey! Hey, Luffy! Stop it!
They're thugs from a nearby town.

183
00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:42.560
They're after whale meat.

184
00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:42.010
What are you trying to do?

185
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:43.770
It belongs to someone else.

186
00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:44.890
If they capture Laboon,

187
00:11:44.890 --> 00:11:48.520
they'd be able to feed their town
for at least two to three years.

188
00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:49.810
Laboon?

189
00:11:49.810 --> 00:11:51.900
That's the name of this whale.

190
00:11:51.900 --> 00:11:57.240
He's an island whale, a species
that only lives in the West Blue.

191
00:11:57.240 --> 00:11:59.990
They're the biggest
whales in the world.

192
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:03.120
I won't let them use him as food.

193
00:12:03.540 --> 00:12:06.870
There's a reason he keeps hitting
himself against the Red Line

194
00:12:06.870 --> 00:12:12.090
and howling toward Reverse Mountain.

195
00:12:12.090 --> 00:12:12.840
A reason?

196
00:12:12.840 --> 00:12:14.050
Yes.

197
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:19.970
He's a whale with a human heart.

198
00:12:20.390 --> 00:12:25.390
And he's been devotedly waiting
for a certain pirate crew...

199
00:12:29.060 --> 00:12:31.270
for fifty long years...

200
00:12:31.730 --> 00:12:36.240
This... is Laboon's story...

201
00:12:49.750 --> 00:12:54.420
One day, while I was on duty
as the lighthouse keeper,

202
00:12:54.420 --> 00:12:58.800
some good-natured pirates
came down Reverse Mountain

203
00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:01.470
to enter the Grand Line.

204
00:13:01.470 --> 00:13:06.100
And a small whale came down too,
seemingly following them.

205
00:13:06.100 --> 00:13:08.680
That was Laboon.

206
00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:13.730
As I said before, the island whale
is the largest whale species,

207
00:13:13.730 --> 00:13:15.400
and only lives in the West Blue.

208
00:13:16.400 --> 00:13:20.400
The pirates had been traveling
with Laboon the entire time,

209
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:27.120
but they left him behind because of
how dangerous the Grand Line is.

210
00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:29.540
But Laboon followed
without them noticing.

211
00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:35.590
Island whales usually travel
with their families in pods,

212
00:13:36.130 --> 00:13:41.050
but I suppose Laboon felt
that the pirates were his family.

213
00:13:41.050 --> 00:13:46.390
Since their ship had broken down,
they stayed here for several months.

214
00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:50.140
We became close friends in that time.

215
00:13:51.770 --> 00:13:54.730
Because of that, on the day
of their departure...

216
00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:57.360
I need to ask you a favor, my friend.

217
00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:59.990
Can you take care of Laboon
for two or three years?

218
00:14:00.530 --> 00:14:04.070
We'll return after sailing
around the world.

219
00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:07.870
Listen up, Laboon.

220
00:14:07.870 --> 00:14:11.460
We're going to enter the Grand Line
and circumnavigate the world.

221
00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:13.870
But please wait for us here.

222
00:14:14.210 --> 00:14:16.130
We're going to a dangerous place.

223
00:14:16.130 --> 00:14:18.460
Too dangerous for you to come along.

224
00:14:19.090 --> 00:14:21.920
Don't worry. Three years
will go by in a flash.

225
00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:23.180
Don't forget...

226
00:14:23.680 --> 00:14:26.430
We'll always be family,
no matter how far apart we are.

227
00:14:30.890 --> 00:14:32.390
Well then, we're setting off.

228
00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:38.230
Guys! We're setting sail!

229
00:14:38.230 --> 00:14:39.780
Hoist the anchor!

230
00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:41.240
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

231
00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:46.700
Laboon!

232
00:14:47.910 --> 00:14:49.990
Wait for us, Laboon!

233
00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:52.450
We promise to return!

234
00:14:52.450 --> 00:14:54.080
Mark my words!

235
00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:09.560
But that was fifty long years ago...

236
00:15:09.560 --> 00:15:10.810
Fifty years?

237
00:15:10.810 --> 00:15:14.180
Laboon's been waiting for those
guys for fifty whole years?

238
00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:18.230
Is that why he continues
to howl and ram into the rocks?

239
00:15:18.230 --> 00:15:19.020
Correct.

240
00:15:28.450 --> 00:15:30.200
This is an amazing canal.

241
00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:33.250
I'm surprised that he's alive
with a hole like this in him.

242
00:15:33.250 --> 00:15:34.870
Was this also your old "whimsy"?

243
00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:36.710
A "doctor's whimsy."

244
00:15:36.710 --> 00:15:37.580
Doctor?

245
00:15:37.580 --> 00:15:39.840
I may not look it,
but yes, I'm a doctor.

246
00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:43.090
I used to run a clinic on
the cape many years ago.

247
00:15:43.090 --> 00:15:45.720
I was also a ship's
doctor for a few years.

248
00:15:45.720 --> 00:15:46.930
Really?

249
00:15:47.430 --> 00:15:49.510
You should be one for our ship!

250
00:15:49.510 --> 00:15:51.310
Don't be ridiculous.

251
00:15:51.310 --> 00:15:55.480
I no longer have the energy to keep
up with you reckless youngsters.

252
00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:58.770
A doctor, huh? That explains why
the whale's insides are like this...

253
00:15:58.770 --> 00:16:00.480
So this is from the treatment?

254
00:16:00.940 --> 00:16:02.480
That's right.

255
00:16:02.480 --> 00:16:08.160
It's impossible to treat a whale
this big from the outside.

256
00:16:08.910 --> 00:16:10.280
I'm opening the doors.

257
00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:22.960
There it is!

258
00:16:22.960 --> 00:16:25.380
The real sky!

259
00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:36.060
Miss Wednesday, what are you...

260
00:16:38.310 --> 00:16:40.480
A whole fifty years, huh?

261
00:16:40.480 --> 00:16:42.940
Those pirates sure are
making him wait...

262
00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:44.190
Idiot.

263
00:16:44.190 --> 00:16:46.280
This is the Grand Line.

264
00:16:46.610 --> 00:16:48.030
They're dead.

265
00:16:48.030 --> 00:16:51.370
They won't come back
no matter how long he waits.

266
00:16:51.370 --> 00:16:54.080
Why are you being so cynical?!

267
00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:56.370
You don't know that for sure!

268
00:16:56.370 --> 00:16:58.210
They could still come back!

269
00:16:58.210 --> 00:17:00.120
It's such a touching story!

270
00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:03.340
A whale believing in his friends'
promise for fifty long years...

271
00:17:03.340 --> 00:17:05.460
Isn't it, pops?!

272
00:17:05.460 --> 00:17:06.800
Yeah...

273
00:17:06.800 --> 00:17:10.050
But unfortunately, reality is cruel.

274
00:17:10.050 --> 00:17:14.680
I heard from a reliable source...

275
00:17:14.680 --> 00:17:17.770
that they fled the Grand Line.

276
00:17:17.770 --> 00:17:19.310
No way...

277
00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:22.230
You're telling me
they left him behind?!

278
00:17:23.480 --> 00:17:25.570
Fled the Grand Line...

279
00:17:25.570 --> 00:17:27.940
So they crossed
the Calm Belt and lived?

280
00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:30.400
Whether they're alive or not,

281
00:17:30.400 --> 00:17:32.860
I doubt they'll ever return.

282
00:17:32.860 --> 00:17:36.080
Seasons. Weather.
Current. Wind direction.

283
00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:38.330
They're all random here.

284
00:17:38.330 --> 00:17:41.710
Common sense is useless
in the Grand Line.

285
00:17:41.710 --> 00:17:46.550
Weak hearts soon succumb
to fear on the Grand Line.

286
00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:50.170
So the weak of heart
chose to run away,

287
00:17:50.170 --> 00:17:54.050
caring more about their lives
than the promise they made...

288
00:17:55.850 --> 00:17:58.600
They abandoned the whale?!

289
00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:01.230
While he's been waiting
here for fifty years?!

290
00:18:01.230 --> 00:18:02.440
That's too cruel!

291
00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:06.230
If you know that,
why haven't you told him?

292
00:18:06.570 --> 00:18:09.360
He can understand
human speech, right?

293
00:18:09.690 --> 00:18:11.030
I did tell him.

294
00:18:11.030 --> 00:18:13.490
I tried to tell him the whole story.

295
00:18:14.070 --> 00:18:16.280
Laboon! Listen up!

296
00:18:16.280 --> 00:18:19.330
I heard that those pirates
have fled the Grand Line.

297
00:18:19.870 --> 00:18:22.210
I know that you were friends,

298
00:18:22.540 --> 00:18:26.210
and that the promise they made
with you was certainly genuine...

299
00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:34.090
But I'm afraid...

300
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.600
they will never return...

301
00:18:56.870 --> 00:18:59.530
Laboon! Listen to me!

302
00:18:59.530 --> 00:19:01.240
They will never–

303
00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:13.010
I understand that you
don't want to believe it...

304
00:19:13.760 --> 00:19:17.140
but you must accept it somehow!

305
00:19:17.800 --> 00:19:18.510
Laboon!

306
00:19:23.060 --> 00:19:24.600
Laboon!

307
00:19:34.860 --> 00:19:40.700
It was on that day that he began
howling at Reverse Mountain

308
00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:44.330
and ramming his body
against the Red Line...

309
00:19:44.330 --> 00:19:46.250
It's as if he's insisting

310
00:19:46.250 --> 00:19:51.000
they will come down the other side
of that wall any day now...

311
00:19:51.590 --> 00:19:52.880
What a whale...

312
00:19:52.880 --> 00:19:55.050
Even though there's
no point in waiting...

313
00:19:55.050 --> 00:19:59.010
He refuses to believe me because if
I'm right, there would be no reason to wait.

314
00:19:59.680 --> 00:20:03.680
He's afraid of that
more than anything.

315
00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:05.980
His home is in the West Blue...

316
00:20:06.390 --> 00:20:08.350
but there's no way
to return from here.

317
00:20:08.350 --> 00:20:14.480
Those pirates were not only his friends,
but his hope for going home.

318
00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:18.490
While I do feel bad for the whale,

319
00:20:18.490 --> 00:20:21.280
they betrayed you, too, right?

320
00:20:23.620 --> 00:20:26.200
Haven't you taken care
of him long enough?

321
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:28.870
Look at the scars on his forehead!

322
00:20:28.870 --> 00:20:34.300
If he continues to ram his head
like that, he'll surely die.

323
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:37.630
It's an odd relationship, but I've
been with him for fifty years.

324
00:20:37.630 --> 00:20:39.680
I can't just stand by
and watch him die.

325
00:20:42.510 --> 00:20:44.140
What's that idiot doing now?

326
00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:45.890
We only looked away for a second...

327
00:20:45.890 --> 00:20:47.850
Does he think he's
a mountain climber?

328
00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:52.270
Gum-Gum...

329
00:20:52.270 --> 00:20:54.360
Bouquet!

330
00:20:54.690 --> 00:20:56.490
Isn't that a mast?

331
00:20:56.490 --> 00:20:58.490
Yep. The one from our ship.

332
00:20:58.490 --> 00:20:59.780
The main mast, yes.

333
00:21:00.110 --> 00:21:02.410
Hey! Don't break the ship!

334
00:21:09.210 --> 00:21:11.670
– What the hell are you doing?!
– What the hell are you doing?!

335
00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:23.550
Wha...?! Hey, kid!

336
00:21:23.930 --> 00:21:26.970
Don't worry! He can't die
from being crushed!

337
00:21:31.770 --> 00:21:32.600
Dummy!

338
00:21:39.360 --> 00:21:40.780
What's he thinking?

339
00:21:44.830 --> 00:21:47.990
Luffy! What the hell
are you trying to do?!

340
00:21:52.830 --> 00:21:53.960
It's a draw!

341
00:21:58.760 --> 00:22:00.050
I'm pretty strong, huh?

342
00:22:02.130 --> 00:22:04.550
Our fight isn't over yet!

343
00:22:04.550 --> 00:22:06.560
We'll have to settle things later!

344
00:22:06.560 --> 00:22:10.140
Your friends might be dead,
but I'll always be your rival!

345
00:22:10.140 --> 00:22:14.350
One day, we definitely gotta
settle this and see who's stronger.

346
00:22:14.350 --> 00:22:18.150
After we go around the Grand Line,
we'll come back to see you again.

347
00:22:19.480 --> 00:22:21.440
When I come back,
we'll finish our fight!

348
00:22:37.040 --> 00:22:38.210
Perfect.

349
00:22:38.210 --> 00:22:42.090
This symbol means
we promise to fight again.

350
00:22:42.090 --> 00:22:48.100
So don't ram into stuff or you'll
erase it before we get back. Got it?!

351
00:22:51.520 --> 00:22:53.270
Alright!

352
00:22:55.150 --> 00:22:56.270
Where'd those guys go?

353
00:22:56.270 --> 00:22:57.730
"Those guys"?

354
00:22:57.730 --> 00:22:59.610
Oh, you mean those two weirdos?

355
00:22:59.610 --> 00:23:01.110
Maybe they ran away?

356
00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:04.400
We never did find out
what their deal was, huh...

357
00:23:07.320 --> 00:23:10.620
Whatever do we do now,
Miss Wednesday?

358
00:23:12.910 --> 00:23:16.670
At the very least, we'll need to
go back and report to the boss...

359
00:23:16.670 --> 00:23:19.420
We were supposed to finish
this mission long ago.

360
00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:23.380
You're right. It would be bad if they
begin to suspect us of treachery.

361
00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:24.510
Indeed.

362
00:23:24.510 --> 00:23:27.840
Since we lost our weapons, we have
to return to base and start over.

363
00:23:27.840 --> 00:23:31.970
If we must. Well then,
let us... begin... Huh?

364
00:23:31.970 --> 00:23:34.310
Um...? Where is...? What?!

365
00:23:34.640 --> 00:23:35.640
What's the matter?

366
00:23:37.190 --> 00:23:37.900
It's gone...

367
00:23:37.900 --> 00:23:38.520
What?

368
00:23:41.270 --> 00:23:42.190
What's this?

369
00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:44.990
You dropped the log pose?!

370
00:23:44.990 --> 00:23:46.700
I apologize, Miss Wednesday!

371
00:23:46.700 --> 00:23:48.990
And we need it to return home...

372
00:23:50.990 --> 00:23:52.120
As it stands–

373
00:23:53.620 --> 00:23:56.000
I-Is that...?!

374
00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:56.710
Huh?

375
00:23:58.290 --> 00:23:59.540
It's...

376
00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:02.460
O-Oh no...

377
00:24:03.380 --> 00:24:04.670
...the Unluckies!

378
00:24:04.670 --> 00:24:05.970
Darn! Are we too late?!

379
00:24:05.090 --> 00:24:08.890
<b>Miss Friday

Mysterious
Vulture Mr. 13

Mysterious
Sea Otter</b>

380
00:24:05.970 --> 00:24:07.050
Mr. 13!

381
00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:08.890
Miss Friday!

382
00:24:09.220 --> 00:24:11.550
Please wait! We can explain!

383
00:24:11.550 --> 00:24:14.270
We'll report to the boss immediately!

384
00:24:28.410 --> 00:24:32.740
Now then! I finally get to
chart out our Grand Line journey.

385
00:24:37.540 --> 00:24:41.420
Alright! I can finally cook up
the elephant bluefin tuna!

386
00:24:41.420 --> 00:24:42.920
Damn...!

387
00:24:43.880 --> 00:24:47.880
What was Luffy thinking,
wrecking our ship! Really...

388
00:24:47.880 --> 00:24:49.180
Hey, Zoro!

389
00:24:49.180 --> 00:24:51.970
Give me a hand!
I'm not exactly a shipwright!

390
00:24:57.890 --> 00:24:59.480
What's with the screaming?

391
00:24:59.480 --> 00:25:01.350
Is all well, Nami?!

392
00:25:01.350 --> 00:25:03.520
If you're hungry, I have
our meal right here!

393
00:25:03.520 --> 00:25:04.320
Time to eat?

394
00:25:04.650 --> 00:25:06.780
Th-The compass is broken!

395
00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:08.990
It's not pointing anywhere!

396
00:25:08.990 --> 00:25:10.660
Hey, you're right.

397
00:25:10.660 --> 00:25:12.780
It keeps spinning.

398
00:25:12.780 --> 00:25:14.450
Whoa! Neat!

399
00:25:15.330 --> 00:25:19.250
Looks like you guys
came here unprepared.

400
00:25:19.250 --> 00:25:22.330
For heaven's sake!
Did you come here to die?

401
00:25:22.790 --> 00:25:23.420
What?

402
00:25:23.420 --> 00:25:24.130
Food?

403
00:25:24.130 --> 00:25:25.960
You'll be eating hay.

404
00:25:25.960 --> 00:25:27.420
I thought I told you...

405
00:25:27.420 --> 00:25:30.840
Common sense is useless in this sea.

406
00:25:30.840 --> 00:25:34.140
It's not that the compass is broken...

407
00:25:34.930 --> 00:25:37.140
Then, is it the magnetic fields?

408
00:25:37.140 --> 00:25:38.220
Correct.

409
00:25:38.220 --> 00:25:43.610
The islands in the Grand Line
are rich in magnetic minerals.

410
00:25:43.610 --> 00:25:46.360
They cause abnormalities
throughout the Grand Line.

411
00:25:46.360 --> 00:25:49.780
Furthermore, the current and wind
patterns are never consistent.

412
00:25:49.780 --> 00:25:53.620
As a navigator, you should know
how terrifying that is.

413
00:25:53.620 --> 00:25:57.830
We'll have no hope of survival without
a way to know our direction...

414
00:25:57.830 --> 00:25:58.790
Yummy!

415
00:25:58.790 --> 00:26:00.910
I-I didn't know! Oh, well...

416
00:26:00.910 --> 00:26:03.540
Hey! That's really bad!
Are we gonna be okay?!

417
00:26:03.540 --> 00:26:06.000
This isn't bad. It's yummy!

418
00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:08.960
Can you guys be quiet
for one second?!

419
00:26:08.960 --> 00:26:12.130
The nose of the elephant
bluefin tuna tastes good!

420
00:26:12.590 --> 00:26:17.600
You need a log pose to travel
around the Grand Line.

421
00:26:17.600 --> 00:26:19.850
Log pose? I've never heard of it.

422
00:26:19.850 --> 00:26:23.850
It's a special compass
that can record magnetism.

423
00:26:23.850 --> 00:26:25.400
Like a weird-looking compass?

424
00:26:25.400 --> 00:26:27.980
Yes, its shape is quite unusual.

425
00:26:27.980 --> 00:26:29.400
Something like this?

426
00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:30.530
Yeah, that's the one.

427
00:26:30.990 --> 00:26:35.910
It's impossible to navigate
the Grand Line without a log pose.

428
00:26:36.660 --> 00:26:38.160
I see.

429
00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:39.910
But hold on a second...

430
00:26:40.410 --> 00:26:41.830
Luffy?

431
00:26:42.210 --> 00:26:44.830
How come you have one?!

432
00:26:46.540 --> 00:26:50.630
Those two weirdos
dropped it on the ship.

433
00:26:50.630 --> 00:26:51.800
They did?

434
00:26:51.800 --> 00:26:53.170
Why'd you hit me?

435
00:26:53.170 --> 00:26:54.130
It felt right.

436
00:26:54.130 --> 00:26:55.090
Fair enough.

437
00:26:56.340 --> 00:26:57.680
So this is a log pose.

438
00:26:57.680 --> 00:26:59.220
There's no dial face.

439
00:26:59.220 --> 00:27:06.810
The magnetic fields of islands in
the Grand Line follow a certain rule:

440
00:27:06.810 --> 00:27:11.990
By recording the magnetism of
two islands pulling against each other,

441
00:27:11.990 --> 00:27:14.490
you can find the route
to the next island.

442
00:27:14.990 --> 00:27:18.160
Since you can't even figure out
your location in this sea,

443
00:27:18.160 --> 00:27:22.000
the magnetic record of the log pose
is the only thing you can depend on.

444
00:27:22.450 --> 00:27:29.130
To begin, you must pick one of
Reverse Mountain's seven magnetic fields.

445
00:27:29.130 --> 00:27:32.050
But no matter which route you take,

446
00:27:32.050 --> 00:27:35.930
the magnetic pulls will eventually
push you onto one route.

447
00:27:35.930 --> 00:27:39.470
And the name of the island
at the end of the voyage is...

448
00:27:39.970 --> 00:27:41.310
Laugh Tale.

449
00:27:41.310 --> 00:27:44.100
It's the last island in the Grand Line.

450
00:27:44.100 --> 00:27:48.310
The only one in history to confirm
its existence is the King of the Pirates.

451
00:27:48.310 --> 00:27:50.440
It's a legendary island.

452
00:27:50.440 --> 00:27:51.820
Laugh Tale...

453
00:27:51.820 --> 00:27:54.650
So is that where the One Piece is?!

454
00:27:54.650 --> 00:27:57.700
Who knows. That's the most
prominent theory,

455
00:27:57.700 --> 00:28:00.410
but no one else has
been able to get there.

456
00:28:00.410 --> 00:28:02.040
Then...

457
00:28:02.040 --> 00:28:03.580
we'll be the first to prove it.

458
00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:09.170
Alright, I'm done!
You guys wanna get going?

459
00:28:09.170 --> 00:28:11.000
You ate the whole thing?!

460
00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:12.670
Whoa! Even the bones are gone.

461
00:28:12.670 --> 00:28:15.970
A log pose, huh? We'd better
take good care of this.

462
00:28:15.970 --> 00:28:18.180
This is the key to
the rest of our journey.

463
00:28:18.180 --> 00:28:19.930
You damn rubber man!

464
00:28:19.930 --> 00:28:22.560
I made Nami such 
a delicious meal and she...

465
00:28:23.350 --> 00:28:26.480
she didn't even have a bite!

466
00:28:41.370 --> 00:28:42.330
What was that for?

467
00:28:42.330 --> 00:28:44.740
Take that, you damn rubber man.

468
00:28:43.660 --> 00:28:44.740
Sanji...

469
00:28:44.740 --> 00:28:46.200
Yes, Nami!

470
00:28:47.040 --> 00:28:50.170
You two should go
cool your heads off!

471
00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:56.550
Hey, hold on a sec...

472
00:28:57.010 --> 00:29:00.300
Wasn't that thing
super-duper important?!

473
00:29:00.300 --> 00:29:02.800
Our precious log pose...

474
00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:05.140
Don't panic. You can have mine.

475
00:29:05.560 --> 00:29:08.060
Think of it as thanks
for helping Laboon.

476
00:29:15.570 --> 00:29:17.570
Man... I thought I was a goner. Huh?

477
00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:23.320
Here, take my hand, dear lady.

478
00:29:23.320 --> 00:29:24.370
Oh, thank you.

479
00:29:24.370 --> 00:29:25.580
Nice day, isn't it?

480
00:29:25.580 --> 00:29:26.370
Hey!

481
00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:28.290
We must ask you a favor.

482
00:29:31.920 --> 00:29:33.210
Whisky Peak?

483
00:29:33.540 --> 00:29:34.750
That's a weird name.

484
00:29:34.750 --> 00:29:35.840
What's that?

485
00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:38.590
That's where we live... um, sir.

486
00:29:38.590 --> 00:29:40.720
What happened to your ship?

487
00:29:40.720 --> 00:29:43.180
I'm afraid it was destroyed.

488
00:29:43.800 --> 00:29:47.890
That's a pretty big favor for someone
who just tried to kill the whale, Mr. 9.

489
00:29:48.310 --> 00:29:50.230
So who are you guys, anyway?

490
00:29:50.230 --> 00:29:51.940
I'm a king.

491
00:29:53.020 --> 00:29:53.980
Liar.

492
00:29:55.230 --> 00:29:56.980
We can't say!

493
00:29:56.980 --> 00:29:59.240
We just want to go back home.

494
00:29:59.240 --> 00:30:02.570
We don't like being
secretive either, but...

495
00:30:02.570 --> 00:30:04.990
...our company motto is "Mystery."

496
00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:07.410
We simply can't tell you
anything about us.

497
00:30:07.740 --> 00:30:11.120
Trusting your good
character, we beg of you!

498
00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:13.500
I assure you, we will return the favor.

499
00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:15.340
Don't do it.

500
00:30:15.340 --> 00:30:18.420
No matter what they say,
they're dishonest people.

501
00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:23.930
By the way, we broke the log pose.
Do you still want a ride?

502
00:30:24.260 --> 00:30:27.470
What?! You broke it?!
That was mine, you know!

503
00:30:27.470 --> 00:30:31.520
You dare act smug while we're being
humble?! You're all stuck here as well!

504
00:30:31.890 --> 00:30:33.310
Oh, I forgot to mention...

505
00:30:33.310 --> 00:30:36.480
We do have a spare,
courtesy of Mr. Crocus.

506
00:30:37.320 --> 00:30:39.480
We beg you people
of such character...

507
00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:42.450
Dammit! This minx is toying with us!

508
00:30:42.780 --> 00:30:44.280
Sure, you can ride with us.

509
00:30:45.700 --> 00:30:47.160
Whisky Peak, right?

510
00:30:47.160 --> 00:30:48.330
Let's go there.

511
00:30:48.330 --> 00:30:49.080
– What?
– Huh?

512
00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:53.290
Hey, are you sure we wanna go out of
our way to take these shady guys?

513
00:30:53.660 --> 00:30:54.710
What's the problem?

514
00:30:54.710 --> 00:30:56.750
Don't sweat the small stuff.

515
00:30:56.750 --> 00:31:01.710
Once you choose your route here,
you won't be able to change it.

516
00:31:01.710 --> 00:31:04.550
If we don't like it,
we'll just go around again.

517
00:31:05.090 --> 00:31:06.470
Is that so...?

518
00:31:07.010 --> 00:31:08.850
So, should we get going?

519
00:31:10.220 --> 00:31:13.310
Since I've made my promise
with the whale, let's sail out.

520
00:31:13.680 --> 00:31:16.060
Who in the world are you?

521
00:31:16.060 --> 00:31:17.020
Me?

522
00:31:17.020 --> 00:31:17.900
I'm...

523
00:31:18.310 --> 00:31:20.480
the man who's gonna be
King of the Pirates!

524
00:31:24.950 --> 00:31:26.530
What a foolish pirate...

525
00:31:29.410 --> 00:31:30.950
You should be good to go.

526
00:31:30.950 --> 00:31:33.000
The log must have
been stored by now.

527
00:31:33.620 --> 00:31:36.080
Is it pointing at the same
direction as the map?

528
00:31:36.080 --> 00:31:36.830
Yep.

529
00:31:37.540 --> 00:31:39.500
It's pointing at Whisky Peak.

530
00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:41.840
See ya, flower guy!

531
00:31:41.840 --> 00:31:43.420
Thanks for the log pose!

532
00:31:43.420 --> 00:31:45.340
Yeah. Have a safe trip!

533
00:31:45.340 --> 00:31:47.970
See ya, too, whale! I'm leaving now!

534
00:31:52.930 --> 00:31:54.890
Full speed ahead...

535
00:31:54.890 --> 00:31:57.270
to Whisky Peak!

536
00:31:57.270 --> 00:31:59.270
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

537
00:32:16.910 --> 00:32:21.790
Could they be the pirates we've been
waiting for all this time...?

538
00:32:21.790 --> 00:32:25.760
That man has a particularly
strange air about him...

539
00:32:28.800 --> 00:32:30.010
don't you think,

540
00:32:30.010 --> 00:32:31.720
Roger?
